    "id": 2,
    "title": "AI Newz Snacks — March 31, 2026",
    "date": "2026-03-31",
    "tags": [
      "Robotaxi",
      "Robots",
      "OpenAI",
      "Apple",
      "Pentagon"
    ],
    "fresh": false,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — March 31, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🚗 Robotaxi Goes \"Mainstream\" (aka Wall Street Bets On It)\n\nOh great, the robo-taxi dream is finally real and we should *definitely* be excited. Waymo just hit 500K paid rides per week—that's a quarter of the way to their end-of-year goal in literally three months. Zoox is expanding coast-to-coast from San Francisco to Vegas, Austin, and Miami.\n\n- Waymo's velocity is kind of absurd: they're doubling deployment speed, half-joking we're basically one software update away from actual autonomous chaos on I-95\n- Zoox is betting the farm on \"purpose-built robotaxis\" (translation: purpose-built to avoid getting sued)\n- When taxi drivers start unionizing *against* robots, you'll know it's real 🤖\n\n**Sources:** [The Robot Report](https://www.therobotreport.com/robotics-news/)\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Physical Intelligence Just Became a Unicorn (The Robot ChatGPT Is Worth $11B)\n\nPhysical Intelligence is raising $1B at an $11B valuation to build \"ChatGPT for robots.\" Founders Fund and Lightspeed are leading. Yes, you read that correctly—a company that teaches robots to do warehouse tasks is worth more than most actual SaaS businesses that make revenue.\n\n- $25B in infrastructure deals hit this week alone, because apparently we need *all* the compute for robots learning to pick things up\n- OpenAI literally *killed* Sora (their video generator) to redirect compute toward robotics\n- The subtext: video generation is so yesterday; robot arms are the new hype vector 🦾\n\n**Sources:** [Crescendo AI News](https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-ai-news-and-updates)\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 Humanoid Robots Are Now Airport Greeters (And They're Multilingual)\n\nSan José's airport deployed \"Jose,\" an IntBot humanoid robot, to help travelers in multiple languages. Because why hire people when you can have a robot that never complains about shift breaks? Also: an AI robot showed up at the Whitehouse EdTech summit with the First Lady.\n\n- These robots aren't stealing *all* the jobs yet, but they're definitely showing up uninvited to events\n- Warehouse robots with agentic AI are now autonomously handling logistics (no human intervention required, which is fine, probably)\n- We're past the \"sci-fi concept\" phase and firmly into \"deployed in actual public spaces\" territory 😅\n\n**Sources:** [The Robot Report](https://www.therobotreport.com/robotics-news/), [RoboticsTomorrow](https://www.roboticstomorrow.com/news/2026/03/31/samsara-to-accelerate-the-future-of-physical-ai-at-humanx-2026/26342/)\n\n---\n\n## 🎬 OpenAI Killed Sora Because Robots > Videos (The Priorities Are Shifting)\n\nOpenAI straight-up discontinued its AI video generator Sora and rerouted all that compute power toward robotics research. No announcement, just gone, redirected to the robot future.\n\n- This is basically admitting: \"Video generation is saturated. Robots are where the real AGI play is\"\n- When billion-dollar companies kill products in their prime, you know the hype cycle is pivoting hard\n- Place your bets: robotics is eating everyone's GPU budgets for the next 12-18 months 🏗️\n\n**Sources:** [The Neuron](https://www.theneuron.ai/ai-news-digests/)\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Apple Is Giving Siri to Claude and Gemini (Antitrust Subtext Intensifies)\n\nApple just opened Siri to Claude and Gemini as extensions in iOS 27. Translation: Apple realized Siri can't keep up, so they're outsourcing the actual intelligence to Anthropic and Google while pretending it's \"choice.\"\n\n- Anthropic gets instant distribution to 2B+ Apple users (casual $100B marketing gift)\n- Google gets a foothold in Apple's ecosystem (weird world we live in)\n- Apple avoids building their own frontier model (smart, honestly) but also admits defeat 🍎\n\n**Sources:** [Crescendo AI News](https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-ai-news-and-updates)\n\n---\n\n## ⚔️ Pentagon vs Anthropic: The Government Wants Skynet, Anthropic Said \"No\"\n\nOver 30 OpenAI and Google DeepMind employees publicly backed Anthropic in a lawsuit against the Pentagon. The Pentagon labeled Anthropic a \"supply-chain risk\" because they *refused* to enable mass surveillance and autonomous weapons.\n\n- This is basically David (Anthropic) vs Goliath (US Defense Dept), except David has backing from the other tech giants' employees\n- The Pentagon wants to buy AI that can surveil citizens and fire weapons autonomously; Anthropic said \"absolutely not\"\n- Meanwhile, three Chinese AI firms allegedly coordinated distillation attacks on Anthropic's models to steal tech 🛡️\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/09/openai-and-google-employees-rush-to-anthropics-defense-in-dod-lawsuit/), [Fortune](https://fortune.com/2026/03/10/google-openai-employees-back-anthropic-legal-fight-military-use-of-ai/), [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/24/anthropic-openai-china-firms-distillation-deepseek.html)\n\n---\n\n## 📊 The Model Avalanche Continues (12 Models In One Week—Kill Me Now)\n\nBetween March 10-16, six companies (OpenAI, Google, xAI, Anthropic, Mistral, Cursor) launched *twelve* distinct models. Four flagship models shipped in a 72-hour window. DeepSeek V4 finally arrived with 1 trillion parameters after months of hype and delays.\n\n- Developer selection cycles are now *monthly*, not quarterly, because models are shipping faster than feature releases\n- This isn't innovation anymore; it's just industrial-scale model spam\n- Eventually we're going to have 10,000 models and nobody will remember which one does what 😵\n\n**Sources:** [AI Unfiltered](https://www.arturmarkus.com/12-ai-models-launched-in-one-week-during-march-10-16-2026-openai-google-xai-anthropic-mistral-and-cursor-compress-developer-selection-cycles-to-monthly-as-frontier-model-releases-pile-up/), [The Decoder](https://the-decoder.com/google-openai-and-anthropic-are-all-bracing-for-deepseeks-next-big-release/), [NxCode](https://www.nxcode.io/resources/news/deepseek-v4-release-specs-benchmarks-2026)\n\n---\n\n**That's your Snacks briefing. Same chaos, faster models, more robots. Same time next week? 🤷**\n"
  },
